This paper is about real-time motion planning for robotic systems, which is a core topic in robotics. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new algorithm that uses convex relaxation and grid-based path selection, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely. The algorithm is designed for robotic systems, which are complex systems that involve control theory, so cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible sub-category. The paper also discusses how to meet curvature constraints, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG).
